<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: REINER HONORED BY STATE TRIAL LAWYERS 
ASSOCIATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County Dist. Atty. Ira Reiner has been named "Outstanding Law 
Enforcement Officer of the Year" by the California Trial Lawyers Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Reiner, the top prosecutor for the county since 1984, was given the award at 
the group's recent annual luncheon in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
Reiner's "integrity and his outstanding record of achievement distinguish him 
in the crime-fighting community, both in the state of California and in the 
nation," said Harvey R. Levine, president of the association. 
</P>
<P>
Expressing his gratitude for the award, Reiner said: "For our criminal justice 
system to have the confidence of the public, it must be even-handed and tough. 
I appreciate the state's trial lawyers for recognizing the necessity of both." 
</P>
</TEXT>
