<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Memorial for Salvadorans Demonstrators carry candles in a procession of 
about 250 Salvadoran activists at Our Lady Queen of Angels Catholic Church 
Monday night to honor those killed over the weekend in the escalating civil war 
in El Salvador. Carrying lighted candles and crosses, participants marched 
around the church and offered prayers. Father Michael Kennedy said the marchers 
called for peace in the war-torn country. MIKE SERGIEFF / Photo for The Times 
</P>
