<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTRIBUTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kudos to those who went to court to seek restraining orders against Los Angeles 
County authorities who extort contributions to the United Way and other 
charities from their employees (Metro, Nov. 3). 
</P>
<P>
My charities are my business. Every year, I and millions of other employees are 
badgered, harassed, coerced and strong-armed to contribute time and money to 
our employers' pet charities. 
</P>
<P>
Irrespective of any verbal or written reassurance, the employees contribute 
mostly out of fear. We feel that our failure to contribute will jeopardize our 
chances for advancement or will aggravate a pre-existing or future disciplinary 
problem. 
</P>
<P>
It is time to ban all solicitations for donations from the workplace and to ban 
any kind of payroll deductions for any charities. 
</P>
<P>
URSULA LOPEZ 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
