<HEADLINE>
<P>
KRAUTHAMMER ON ISRAEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Krauthammer joins such notable syndicated columnists as William F. Buckley, 
George Will, Patrick Buchanan and others in taking his opportunity to stroke 
Israel. He devotes his entire column to pointing out that Israel should only 
negotiate with Palestinian "insiders" and not those Palestinians outside of the 
occupied territories. This despite the fact that Palestinians, wherever found, 
are almost 100% in favor of the PLO representing their interests. 
</P>
<P>
Krauthammer could well have pointed out that Israel has consistently violated 
the human rights of the Palestinians in the occupied territories. He could have 
written of deportations, confiscation of property, demolition of homes of those 
suspected of throwing stones, appropriation of land, midnight visits by Israeli 
troops battering down doors, concentration in camps of thousands without charge 
or trial, beatings of prisoners by soldiers and shooting indiscriminately into 
crowds when confronted by stone throwers. 
</P>
<P>
But our columnists know which side butters their syndications. 
</P>
<P>
These "honorable" writers are able to discern human rights violations in the 
Soviet Union, Cuba, Panama, China and any number of other countries. However, 
their pens dry up and their word processor screens are blank when they have an 
opportunity to bring, via their columns, some slight indictment of Israel for 
the violations visited on Palestinians. 
</P>
<P>
It is truly unthinkable that many of our most noted figures of the media, 
together with our Administration and Congress, have become toadies to Israel 
and are unable to bring themselves to write the truth as Americans know it. 
</P>
<P>
LOWELL E. ENTELL 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
