<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A system of cash payments to University of Minnesota football and basketball 
players that began under football Coach Joe Salem continued after Lou Holtz 
took over, fired university administrator Luther Darville testified. Darville 
also said that basketball Coach Clem Haskins knew of the payments. 
</P>
<P>
Darville, who is being tried on swindling charges in Minneapolis, said he never 
discussed the payments with Holtz. 
</P>
<P>
Holtz and Salem have denied any knowledge of payments to athletes, as has 
Haskins. 
</P>
<P>
Darville headed the Office of Minority and Special Students until he was fired 
in April 1988. 
