<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MALONE, STOCKTON LEAD JAZZ TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Karl Malone had 33 points and 16 rebounds and John Stockton had 30 points and 
16 assists Monday night to lead the Utah Jazz to a 106-93 victory over the 
Washington Bullets at Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
The Jazz led 50-44 at halftime as both teams shot poorly. Utah outscored 
Washington, 16-7, to start the second half to take a 66-51 lead. Stockton had 
five points during the run, Malone had four and Bob Hansen made a three-point 
shot. 
</P>
<P>
Ledell Eackles led the Bullets with 24 points, but Washington's two leading 
scorers, Jeff Malone and Bernard King, finished with four and seven points, 
respectively. Malone averaged 27.5 points as the Bullets won five of their 
first six games, and King averaged 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
The Bullets scored the first seven points of the fourth quarter to close to 
79-70 with 9:45 remaining, but that was as close as they got. 
</P>
<P>
Atlanta 112, Orlando 104 -- Dominique Wilkins scored 34 points and Moses Malone 
had 28 to lead the Hawks in front of 15,077 at the Orlando Arena. 
</P>
<P>
Atlanta led, 102-99, with 2:15 left, then outscored the Magic, 10-5, to win 
their second consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
Orlando had several chances in the final minutes, but missed eight layups in 
the fourth quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
