<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH OFFICIAL CHOSEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush will nominate Martin Gerry of Bethesda, Md., to be assistant 
secretary for planning and evaluation in the Department of Health and Human 
Services, the White House announced Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
UNITED STATES -- GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS; DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES 
(U.S.) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111489-0074 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 134462 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 14, 1989, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 22; Column 1; National Desk 
</P>
