<P>
FALL AT 60 M.P.H. LANDS SKYDIVER IN HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FRANKFORT, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A skydiver practicing over Municipal Airport here was seriously injured when 
his main parachute failed and he hit the ground at 60 m.p.h., authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Kivett, 41, was taken to Methodist Hospital in Indianapolis, where his 
condition was described as serious but stable. Before the accident Sunday, he 
was practicing a stunt that involved using a small chute to give the illusion 
of free fall. The diver later opens the main chute for returning to the ground. 
</P>
