VALLEY EARNINGS: PERCEPTRONICS REPORTS PROFIT IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Perceptronics Inc., the Woodland Hills maker of computer-simulation training 
systems for the military, reported net income of $378,110 for the second 
quarter that ended Sept. 30, compared to a net loss of $205,176 a year earlier. 
Perceptronics said its total revenue fell about 3% for the period, to $7.4 
million from $7.6 million a year before. 
</P>
<P>
For the six-month period, Perceptronics said its net income tripled, to 
$491,706 from $163,441 in the prior period. The company's half-year total 
revenue increased about 2% to $14.1 million from $13.9 million a year earlier. 
</P>
