</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Ives Laboratories said its third-quarter profit tumbled 52% from a year 
earlier on an 11% decline in sales. 
</P>
<P>
St. Ives, a Chatsworth producer of shampoos and other personal-care products, 
said its net income in the quarter that ended Sept. 30 dropped to $590,532 from 
$1.23 million a year earlier. Its sales fell to $25.3 million from $28.5 
million. 
</P>
<P>
