<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kramer Kin Is Miss Golden Globe: The Hollywood Foreign Press Assn. has named 
its 1990 Miss Golden Globe. She is Katharine Kramer, the 20-year-old 
singer-actress daughter of director Stanley Kramer. She will appear at various 
group events, including the 47th annual Golden Globe Awards Jan. 20. Kramer has 
appeared in a one-woman show, "The Colors of Myself," and has a two-week return 
date at the Hollywood Roosevelt Cinegrill coming up in January following an 
earlier sellout engagement there. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
