<HEADLINE>
<P>
ASK DR. RUTH: WORLDS APART: HE TAKES MANHATTAN, SHE TAKES THE FARM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. RUTH WESTHEIMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Q. I am in my late 60s, my lady is in her mid-70s. The age difference is of no 
importance, but our life styles come between us. She is happy on a ranch two 
states away; I like living in a city where I have lived for 20 years and have 
activities, associations, a few friends. She is warm and hospitable; I am more 
introverted and solitude-seeking. 
</P>
<P>
Her children know about our friendship, mine do not. I can't ask her to leave 
her country life, and I don't want to leave my urban one. We are both 
comfortably well-off. How do we arrange our future? No one has ever made me as 
happy as she does, and my company seems to be very pleasing to her. 
</P>
<P>
A. What's the rush to settle down in one place or the other? If you are well 
enough fixed for income, you can spend time with each other sometimes in her 
place, sometimes in yours. That sounds sensible, but something keeps the two of 
you from adopting this simple plan, or rather letting yourselves drift into it. 
</P>
<P>
It would seem that you each have preoccupations connected with your places of 
residence. You mean so much to each other, but not enough to give up your 
interests. In fact, your interests are more interesting to you than your 
affection for each other. This is no crime. It is a good thing to have a life 
you like living, concerns that keep you occupied. You are not ready to accept 
living out on her ranch, but maybe in a while it will seem a pleasant life and 
your city preoccupations may not seem so important. Or the pleasures of living 
in town may captivate her. Why not go along as you are for a while, and find 
out what happens? 
</P>
<P>
Q. I am 60 and I have been stimulating myself to orgasm regularly since 
puberty. At present I would say I do this about six times a week. Is this 
likely to impair my future health? 
</P>
<P>
A. No. There is no medical evidence that doing this has any health effect at 
all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111489-0170 </DOCNO>
