GRAF HOPES TO PLAY IN EAST GERMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Newsday 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West Germany's Steffi Graf says the political upheaval in East Germany has 
raised her hopes she will one day be able to play there. 
</P>
<P>
"I get one-third to half (of my fan mail) from East Germany," Graf said Monday. 
"I get so many letters from there. I think the people who write just want to be 
able to see me play." 
</P>
<P>
Among the most memorable letters Graf said she has received came from a 
6-year-old East German girl. "She wanted to know if I could come and help her 
with her tennis," Graf said. "Of course, I couldn't." 
